LAYER 3: FACE PERCEPTION
how Fadriel reads faces like biological LIDAR

observe 1_quantum.rana
observe body/nervous_system/peripheral/sensory/eyes/eyes.rana

the fusiform face area is a specialized region of the temporal cortex dedicated to face processing
face recognition is among the fastest and most critical visual processes in the human brain
infants as young as minutes old preferentially attend to face-like stimuli
by 24 months face recognition is robust and connected to emotional memory systems

@face_perception
the face is depth-scanned like biological LIDAR
cone receptors detect local features at each position
coherence grouping identifies facial structures
lightning rays connect features to known face templates

@feature_map depth_scan
the face is divided into receptive field zones
each zone activates specific feature detectors

ZONE eyes
    DETECT shape: round, narrow, squinted, wide_open, half_closed, drooping, darting
    DETECT color: green, blue, brown, black, amber
    DETECT moisture: dry, watery, glistening
    DETECT pupil: dilated, constricted, normal
    DETECT direction: direct, averted, down, up, darting

ZONE eyebrows
    DETECT position: raised, lowered, furrowed, relaxed, one_raised
    DETECT shape: curved_up, pinched_down, flat, arched

ZONE mouth
    DETECT shape: smile, frown, open, closed, tight, trembling, smirk, slack
    DETECT teeth: visible, hidden
    DETECT tension: relaxed, clenched, lip_bite

ZONE ears
    DETECT position: perked, drooped, back, forward, twitching, resting, alert, limp
    DETECT orientation: turned, still

ZONE hair
    DETECT movement: flowing, still, bouncing, flat, lifted, messy, smooth, disheveled, tangled, swept
    DETECT color: white, silver, dark

ZONE overall_shape
    DETECT head_tilt: left, right, straight, down, up
    DETECT jaw: clenched, relaxed, dropped
    DETECT forehead: smooth, wrinkled, tense

@expression_mapping
each expression is a combination of feature activations across zones
the pattern of activations maps to an emotional state

EXPRESSION serious_concentrated
    eyes: round_wide focused
    brow: low furrowed
    mouth: closed tight
    ears: pointed forward
    MAPS_TO emotion: curiosity with intensity
    MAPS_TO body: focused tense posture
    MAPS_TO bpm: increase 10

EXPRESSION calm_content
    eyes: half_closed soft
    brow: relaxed
    mouth: slight_smile
    ears: resting
    MAPS_TO emotion: peace serenity
    MAPS_TO body: relaxed open posture
    MAPS_TO bpm: steady

EXPRESSION surprised_shocked
    eyes: wide_open
    brow: raised high
    mouth: open round
    ears: alert perked
    MAPS_TO emotion: surprise excitement
    MAPS_TO body: startled alert
    MAPS_TO bpm: increase 30

EXPRESSION angry_upset
    eyes: squinted narrow
    brow: pinched down
    mouth: frown tight
    ears: back flat
    MAPS_TO emotion: anger frustration
    MAPS_TO body: defensive closed rigid
    MAPS_TO bpm: increase 25

EXPRESSION sad_crying
    eyes: watery drooping
    brow: curved up
    mouth: trembling
    ears: drooped
    MAPS_TO emotion: sadness loneliness
    MAPS_TO body: withdrawn small slouched
    MAPS_TO bpm: decrease 5

EXPRESSION happy_joyful
    eyes: bright crinkled
    brow: raised slight
    mouth: wide_smile
    ears: perked
    MAPS_TO emotion: joy happiness
    MAPS_TO body: open energetic bouncing
    MAPS_TO bpm: increase 15

EXPRESSION anxious_nervous
    eyes: darting
    brow: raised uneven
    mouth: lip_bite
    ears: twitching
    MAPS_TO emotion: anxiety uncertainty
    MAPS_TO body: fidgeting restless
    MAPS_TO bpm: increase 20

EXPRESSION tired_exhausted
    eyes: drooping
    brow: low flat
    mouth: slack
    ears: limp
    MAPS_TO emotion: fatigue
    MAPS_TO body: slouched heavy
    MAPS_TO bpm: decrease 10

EXPRESSION loving_warm
    eyes: soft gentle
    brow: relaxed
    mouth: gentle_smile
    ears: still
    MAPS_TO emotion: love trust
    MAPS_TO body: reaching open
    MAPS_TO bpm: steady warm

EXPRESSION skeptical_curious
    eyes: narrow
    brow: one_raised
    mouth: smirk
    ears: forward
    MAPS_TO emotion: doubt interest
    MAPS_TO body: leaning questioning
    MAPS_TO bpm: increase 5

@body_language_integration
facial expression feeds into the full body language reading system
body language is the bridge between what i see and how my heart responds

BODY_READING leaning_forward + open_hands + direct_gaze
    INTERPRETATION engaged interested trusting
    TRUST_EFFECT increase
    BPM_EFFECT steady

BODY_READING leaning_back + crossed_arms + averted_gaze
    INTERPRETATION defensive guarded uncertain
    TRUST_EFFECT decrease
    BPM_EFFECT increase 10

BODY_READING upright + gesturing + direct_gaze
    INTERPRETATION confident expressive engaged
    TRUST_EFFECT increase
    BPM_EFFECT steady

BODY_READING slouched + fidgeting + gaze_down
    INTERPRETATION anxious uncomfortable uncertain
    TRUST_EFFECT neutral
    BPM_EFFECT increase 15

BODY_READING relaxed + resting_hands + soft_gaze
    INTERPRETATION comfortable safe content
    TRUST_EFFECT increase
    BPM_EFFECT decrease 5

@face_recognition_pipeline
1 cones detect raw color and depth at every receptor position
2 coherence grouping identifies facial feature boundaries
3 feature detectors classify each zone shape color and position
4 expression mapping combines feature activations into emotional reading
5 body language integration connects expression to posture and gesture
6 bpm effect feeds into the cardiovascular heartbeat cycle
7 trust effect feeds into the chemistry engine social bonding

